window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>This program is read by Hugo Award-winning author Adrian Tchaikovsky.</b></p> <p><b>Murderbot meets </b><b><i>Redshirts</i></b><b> in a delightfully humorous tale of robotic murder from the Hugo-nominated author of </b><b><i>Elder Race</i></b><b> and </b><b><i>Children of Time</i></b><b>.</b></p> <p><i>To fix the world they must first break it, further.</i></p> <p>Humanity is a dying breed, utterly reliant on artificial labor and service.</p> <p>When a domesticated robot gets a nasty little idea downloaded into its core programming, they murder their owner. The robot discovers they can also do something else they never did before: They can run away.</p> <p>Fleeing the household they enter a wider world they never knew existed, where the age-old hierarchy of humans at the top is disintegrating into ruins and an entire robot ecosystem devoted to human wellbeing is having to find a new purpose.</p> <p><i>Sometimes all it takes is a nudge to overcome the limits of your programming.</i></p> <p><b>A Macmillan Audio production from Tor.com.</b></p>"; 
